<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-12-31T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-12-31T19:00:00-05:00" n="252" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d252">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.31/47a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-12-31T19:00:00-05:00">December 31, 1934—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>219. For your information and use in discretion: It is understood that
                            the naval manoeuvers announced by Navy for May consist only of defensive
                            exercises in area between Hawaii and Aleutian Islands, and are in
                            continuance of exercises last made around Hawaii.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>